<BLOCK2><TI>The Parties</TI>
<P>2. The plaintiff, Al Way (<BOLD>&ldquo;Way&rdquo;</BOLD>), is an individual residing in the City of Waterloo, in the Province of Ontario.</P>
<P>3. The plaintiffs, Kingsley Financial Inc. (<BOLD>&ldquo;Kingsley&rdquo;</BOLD>) and Triumph Financial Holdings Inc. (<BOLD>&ldquo;Triumph&rdquo;</BOLD>), are corporations incorporated pursuant to the laws of the Province of Ontario. Way is an officer and director of both Kingsley and Triumph.</P>
<P>4. The defendant, Gordon Schembri (<BOLD>&ldquo;Schembri&rdquo;</BOLD>), is an individual residing in the City of Waterloo, in the Province of Ontario.</P>
<P>5. The defendants, Schembri Financial Limited (<BOLD>&ldquo;Schembri Financial&rdquo;</BOLD>), 41 Columbia Inc., King &amp; Columbia Inc. and 69 Columbia St. Inc. are corporations incorporated pursuant to the laws of the Province of Ontario. Schembri is an officer and director of each of these companies.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI>The Shareholder Agreement</TI>
<P>6. On or about April 2, 2008, Kingsley, Schembri Financial, Triumph, Way and Schembri entered into a shareholder agreement in respect of the shares of Triumph (the <BOLD>&ldquo;Shareholder Agreement&rdquo;</BOLD>).</P>
<P>7. The plaintiffs state that Schembri Financial and Schembri are in breach of the Shareholder Agreement, and are liable to pay the plaintiffs damages arising out of this breach. Particulars of the breaches of the Shareholder Agreement by Schembri Financial and Schembri include pursuing certain prospective real estate development opportunities in the Regional Municipality of Waterloo, without first offering such prospective real estate development opportunities to both Kingsley Financial Inc. and Triumph Financial Holdings Inc.</P>
<P>8. On or about April 30, 2010, 41 Columbia Inc. purchased 39 Columbia and 41 Columbia.</P>
<P>9. On or about August 2, 2011, King &amp; Columbia Inc. purchased 359 King.</P>
<P>10. On or about September 9, 2011, 69 Columbia St. Inc purchased 69 Columbia.</P>
<P>11. In breach of the Shareholder Agreement, neither Schembri Financial nor Schembri presented Kingsley or Triumph with the prospective real estate development opportunities in respect of 39 Columbia, 41 Columbia, 359 King and 69 Columbia.</P>
<P>12. As a result of the failure of Schembri Financial and Schembri to present Kingsley and Triumph with the prospective real estate development opportunities in respect of 39 Columbia, 41 Columbia, 359 King and 69 Columbia, the plaintiffs have suffered loss and damages.</P>
<P>13. The plaintiffs claim that 41 Columbia Inc. and Schembri hold title and beneficial interest in 39 Columbia and 41 Columbia in trust the plaintiffs.</P>
<P>14. The plaintiffs claim that King &amp; Columbia Inc. and Schembri hold title and beneficial interest in 359 King in trust for the plaintiffs.</P>
<P>15. The plaintiffs claim that 69 Columbia St. Inc. and Schembri hold title and beneficial interest in 69 Columbia in trust the plaintiffs.</P>
<P>16. The plaintiffs propose that the trial of this action be held at the City of Kitchener, in the Province of Ontario.</P>
