<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I">AFFIDAVIT OF GORDON SCHEMBRI</TI>
<P>I, Gordon Schembri, of the City of Toronto, in the Province of Ontario, MAKE OATH AND SAY:</P>
<P>1. I am a Defendant to this action and a representative of the other Defendants to this action, and, as such, have knowledge of the matters contained in this affidavit, unless advised by others, in which case I have stated the source of my information and do verily believe it to be true.</P>
<P>2. The Corporate Defendants are corporations controlled by me.</P>
<P>3. I will be filing in support of the Defendants' motion certain affidavits sworn and filed by me in connection with various interlocutory proceedings that have taken place in an action commenced by me and companies controlled by me against Way and others bearing court file No. C-42-11 (the &ldquo;Main Action&rdquo;). These affidavits will be filed separately and are relied upon to support the relief sought herein and to provide the full factual background that gave rise to the appointment of a Receiver against the Triumph Subsidiaries and the sale of certain properties including 359 King Street Waterloo which is the subject matter of this action.</P>
<P>4. Filed in support of this motion and filed separately are:
<P1>(a) the motion record that the Plaintiffs filed in the Main Action seeking an order, inter alia, for the appointment of a Receiver over the Triumph Subsidiaries, which includes my affidavit sworn May 14, 2010 (&ldquo;May Affidavit&rdquo;);</P1>
<P1>(b) a copy of my affidavit sworn September 5, 2010, again in support of a Receivership motion in the Main Action;</P1>
<P1>(c) the motion materials filed by the Plaintiffs in the Main Action wherein an order approving the sale transaction relating to 359 King St. West was sought. That motion material contains a copy of my affidavit sworn June 7, 2011, filed in support of the said motion, together with exhibits;</P1>
<P1>(d) the affidavit of Michael Gayed sworn June 29, 2011, in support of an order staying the order of Master Mesbur pending appeal to the Court of Appeal;</P1>
<P1>(e) my June 7, 2011, affidavit regarding the Sales Process.</P1></P>
<P>[Missing text]
<P1>(a) The Plaintiff, Kingsley Financial Inc. (&ldquo;Kingsley&rdquo;) would own 55% of the shares of Triumph Financial and Schembri Financial would own the remaining 45%;</P1>
<P1>(b) Kingsley received 55% of the said share because it was recognized that Way and his entity would be required to fund and finance any development without contribution from me. Schembri Financial received 45% in recognition of my offer to assemble, acquire and rezone and obtain all required permits for the properties;</P1>
<P1>(c) Each of Way and me, or our respective nominees were directors;</P1>
<P1>(d) Way was president and I was secretary-treasurer;</P1>
<P1>(e) Way, as President, had the ability to sign all contracts on behalf of Triumph Financial, except in respect of matters relating to land acquisition, mortgage financing, construction budgets and project feasibility, which required the signatures of both Way and me or our designates;</P1>
<P1>(f) Each of the directors had one vote and Way, as chairman, did not have any additional or casting vote. Accordingly, if Way and I did not agree, then the board of directors would be deadlocked;</P1>
<P1>(g) Unanimous shareholder approval was required for Triumph Financial:
<P2>(i) to directly or indirectly make any loans or advances, or invest in or give security for, or guarantee the debts of any other Corporation or person;</P2></P1></P>
