<P><BOLD>70.</BOLD> Contrary to paragraph 9(d) of the Schembri ROFR SJ Affidavit, the JV Agreement did not require a written agreement for an increase in the budget; it simply required an agreement.</P>
<P><BOLD>71.</BOLD> As discussed in below, Schembri participated in and agreed to: (a) changes to the design of the building (including changes required by the City); and (b) the various budgets prepared in connection with the changes to the design of the building.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI>The &ldquo;5 and 5&rdquo;</TI>
<P><BOLD>72.</BOLD> Schembri and I agreed that 172 would pay:
<P1>(a) five percent (5%) of construction costs for office administration; and</P1>
<P1>(b) five percent (5%) of construction costs and office administration as profit;</P1>
(jointly, the <BOLD>&ldquo;5 and 5&rdquo;).</BOLD> The 5 and 5 is shown on the second page of the JV Pro Forma.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI>Determination of Profit</TI>
<P><BOLD>73.</BOLD> Paragraph 1(5) of the JV Agreement states:
<QUOTE><P><EM>&ldquo;Proportionate Share&rdquo; means with respect to each Joint Venturer its undivided interest in the profit made from the completed project and in the Joint Venture, expressed as a percentage</EM>. <BOLD><EM>Each Joint Venturer shall have a Fifty (50%) percent share of the profit as may be determined by [172] acting reasonably and in accordance with General Accounting Principals</EM></BOLD> <EM>[sic]</EM> <BOLD>(&ldquo;<EM>GAAP</EM>&rdquo;).</BOLD> (emphasis added)</P></QUOTE></P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI>Distribution of Funds</TI>
<P><BOLD>74.</BOLD> Paragraph 2(12) of the JV Agreement states:
<QUOTE><P><EM>When surplus funds from receipts of the Joint Venturer [sic] are available which are not required for the normal operation of the Joint Venture they shall be applied in the following order:</EM></P>
<P><EM>(a) first, to pay any expenses or charges due in respect of the Lands and Project;</EM></P>
<P><EM>(b) secondly, to pay any interest incurring at the rate of prime plus 3% on the item set out in 15(a) [sic] made by the Joint Venturers outside of any third party financing; and</EM></P>
<P><EM>(c) thirdly, to distribute any balance remaining between the Joint Venturers in accordance with their Proportionate Shares</EM>.</P></QUOTE></P></BLOCK2></BLOCK1>
<BLOCK1><N>6</N><TI>172 Acquires JV Lands</TI>
<P><BOLD>75.</BOLD> In furtherance of the JV Agreement, arrangements were made to extend the closing date for each of the three properties that Schembri did not have the financing to close (namely, 341 King Street, 349 King Street and 340 Spruce Street, Waterloo). Such arrangements included payment of a further deposit in the amount of:
<P1>(a) $20,000 in connection with 340 Spruce Street, Waterloo; and</P1>
<P1>(b) $5,000 in connection with 349 King Street, Waterloo.</P1></P>
<P>Copies of the documents evidencing the arrangements made to extend the closing date for each of these three properties are attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;19&rdquo;.</BOLD></P>
<P><BOLD>76.</BOLD> Also in furtherance of the JV Agreement, I arranged for an increase in my company's line of credit with CIBC (the <BOLD>&ldquo;CIBC LoC Increase&rdquo;)</BOLD> in order to complete the acquisition of the JV Lands by 172. A copy of the agreement providing for the CIBC LoC Increase is attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;20&rdquo;.</BOLD></P>
