<BLOCK1><N>12</N><TI>The Triumph Deal</TI>
<P><BOLD>109.</BOLD> On January 29, 2008, Schembri, Schembri's father, Heimbecker, Patterson, Volpini and I met in the boardroom at Jamesway's offices to discuss a deal between Schembri and me for the development of the Waterloo Lands and the London Lands (the <BOLD>&ldquo;January 2008 Meeting&rdquo;).</BOLD></P>
<P><BOLD>110.</BOLD> At the January 2008 Meeting, Schembri and I agreed to a deal (the <BOLD>&ldquo;Triumph Deal&rdquo;)</BOLD> whereby:
<P1>(a) we would incorporate Triumph as a holding company, in which I would have a fifty-five percent (55%) interest and Schembri would have a forty-five percent (45%) interest;</P1>
<P1>(b) we would incorporate subsidiaries of Triumph to acquire and develop the Waterloo Lands and the London Lands in the manner that we were developing the JV Lands (namely, Premier doing the design work in conjunction with various consultants, and Jamesway doing the project management, including the general conditions); and</P1>
<P1>(c) Schembri would look for other lands in Kitchener and Waterloo for us to acquire and develop.</P1></P>
<P><BOLD>111.</BOLD> To be clear, at the January 2008 Meeting I did not agree to either:
<P1>(a) fund the development of the properties to be acquired through subsidiaries of Triumph; or</P1>
<P1>(b) guarantee third party financing for the development of such properties.</P1></P></BLOCK1>
<BLOCK1><N>13</N><TI>Actions Taken in Accordance with the Triumph Deal</TI>
<P><BOLD>112</BOLD>. Following the January 2008 Meeting and prior to the execution of the Shareholder Agreement Schembri and I acted in accordance with Triumph Deal.</P>
<P><BOLD>113.</BOLD> Certain of the actions taken by us included the following:
<P1>(a) Schembri provided an analysis for the renovation of an apartment building located at 137 University Avenue West, Waterloo, which I incorporated into my pro forma template that we subsequently went back and forth on;</P1>
<P1>(b) Schembri received a financing proposal for the Waterloo Lands;</P1>
<P1>(c) Schembri executed an amendment to the London Lands Purchase Agreement dated February 6, 2008;</P1>
<P1>(d) Schembri extended closing dates for the Waterloo Lands;</P1>
<P1>(e) Schembri and I considered an opportunity for a property locatedat Bricker and Ezra in Waterloo;</P1>
<P1>(f) Schembri prepared pro formas in the format of my template for:
<P2>(i) each of the Triumph Lands;</P2>
<P2>(ii) 137 University Avenue West, Waterloo; and</P2>
<P2>(iii) 534 Mariner Road, Kitchener; and</P2></P1>
<P1>(g) Schembri entered into agreements of purchase and sale for:
<P2>(i) 137 University Avenue West, Waterloo; and</P2>
<P2>(ii) 534 Mariner Road, Kitchener;</P2></P1></P>
<P>Copies of the documents evidencing the foregoing actions are attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;41&rdquo;.</BOLD></P>
<P><BOLD>114.</BOLD> Ultimately, Schembri and I did not pursue these development opportunities.</P></BLOCK1>
<BLOCK1><N>14</N><TI>Incorporation of Triumph and 359 King</TI>
<P><BOLD>115.</BOLD> Schembri and I incorporated Triumph and 359 King on or about February 28, 2008. Both myself and Schembri are directors and officers of Triumph and 359 King; I am the President and Schembri is the Secretary-Treasurer. Triumph is the sole shareholder of 359 King. Copies of the documents relating to the incorporation of Triumph are attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;42&rdquo;.</BOLD> Copies of the documents relating to the incorporation of 359 King are attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;43&rdquo;.</BOLD></P>
<P><BOLD>116.</BOLD> In connection with the incorporations of Triumph and 359 King, Schembri and I executed banking documents with CIBC. Copies of these banking documents are attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;44&rdquo;.</BOLD></P>
<P><BOLD>117.</BOLD> The sole business and purpose of 359 King was to design, construct and sell a condominium development on the Waterloo Lands. The preliminary budget to develop the Waterloo Lands was $28,000,000.</P></BLOCK1>
<BLOCK1><N>15</N><TI>JV Tendering and Awarding of Contracts</TI>
<P><BOLD>118.</BOLD> Around the time that 172 secured construction financing for the JV Project, Jamesway began the process of: (a) tendering; (b) evaluating bids submitted; and (c) awarding contracts.</P>
<P><BOLD>119.</BOLD> The tendering process involved creating an &ldquo;FTP&rdquo; site and contacting various trades inviting them to tender. Based on the documents listed in the Way Main Action AoD (defined in paragraph 293), Allison Craine, a project co-ordinator for Jamesway, appears to have been the primary point person in contacting various trades during the tendering process.</P>
<P><BOLD>120.</BOLD> Following the tendering process, Jamesway evaluated the bids submitted by various trades in respect of specific activities relating to the construction of the JV Approved Building Design. Based on the documents listed in the Way Main Action AoD and to the best of my recollection, the then Jamesway employees involved in the process of tendering, evaluating bids and awarding contracts included (in alphabetical order) Rob Corsi, Allison Craine, Jeff King, Ryan Morrison and Steve Silva.</P>
<P><BOLD>121.</BOLD> Schembri was actively involved in the process of tendering, evaluating bids and awarding contracts.</P>
<P><BOLD>122.</BOLD> Evidence of certain of Schembri's involvement in this process appears in the Schembri April 2010 Affidavit at paragraphs 62 to 66, wherein Schembri states:
<P1>(a) he was &ldquo;responsible for retaining trades to perform the flooring, drywalling, masonry and millwork&rdquo;;</P1>
<P1>(b) he &ldquo;retained Olympia Tile to supply the tile and The Source to supply the laminate&rdquo;;</P1>
<P1>(c) he &ldquo;retained Balkan Factory and Mike's Hardwood Flooring to install the tile and the laminate&rdquo;;</P1>
