<P><BOLD>129.</BOLD> In addition to the differences shown in the table above, the City required through the site plan approval process, among other things:
<P1>(a) more landscaping features;</P1>
<P1>(b) increasing the height of the exterior of the building that was to be cladded with masonry stone (as opposed to stucco), as well as incorporating masonry stone into the parking garage;</P1>
<P1>(c) more pronounced massing articulation on all elevations by, among other things, recessing, &ldquo;step backs&rdquo; and terracing; and</P1>
<P1>(d) enhanced stucco detailing;</P1>
as evidenced by Exhibit 32 and Exhibit 33 (as marked in paragraphs 90 and 91).</P>
<P><BOLD>130.</BOLD> In short, the JV Approved Building Design is materially different from the JV Pro Forma Building Design; and those differences impacted the budget materially.</P>
<P><BOLD>131.</BOLD> As stated in paragraph 101 above, Jamesway prepared a construction budget for what became the JV Approved Building Design. Subsequently, Jamesway updated the construction budget from time to time. To the best of my recollection Jeff King and Steve Silva were involved in doing so. Schembri participated in preparing these budgets. Copies of the various construction budgets for the JV Approved Building Design are attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;48&rdquo;.</BOLD></P>
<P><BOLD>132.</BOLD> Schembri admits receiving the construction budgets dated January 21 and February 26, 2009. However, Schembri alleges that he did not approve these budgets at the time that they were presented to him. Not only did Schembri approve the budgets relating to the JV Approved Building, he was involved in their preparation. Moreover, Schembri never told me at any time that he disapproved of any of the budgets for the JV Approved Building Design.</P>
<P><BOLD>133.</BOLD> I relied on Schembri's direct involvement in the JV Project (including the approval of the budgets relating to the JV Approved Building Design), when: (a) entering into the Kingsett Commitment and the CIBC Commitment totaling nearly $20,000,000 (that I personally guaranteed along with several of my companies); and (b) obtaining the JV Building Permit (defined in paragraph 134 below).</P></BLOCK1>
