<BLOCK1><N>21</N><TI>Triumph Completes Purchase of Waterloo Lands</TI>
<P><BOLD>157.</BOLD> Following execution by Schembri of various waivers, amendments, extensions and assignments, 359 King completed the acquisition of the Waterloo Lands on or about April 25, 2008. Copies of those documents along with the reporting letters of Volpini are attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;56&rdquo;.</BOLD></P>
<P><BOLD>158.</BOLD> The acquisition of the Waterloo Lands was funded as follows:
<P1>(a) $1,950,000 from Cameron Stephens Financial Corporation <BOLD>(&ldquo;CSFC&rdquo;);</BOLD> and</P1>
<P1>(b) the balance of $426,602.44 from KFI.</P1></P>
<P>In connection with (a) above, 359 King granted CSFC a mortgage over the Waterloo Lands in the amount of $2,000,000<FOOTNOTE><FREEFORM><P>CSFC held back $50,000 of the mortgage amount.</P></FREEFORM></FOOTNOTE> (the <BOLD>&ldquo;CSFC Mortgage&rdquo;).</BOLD> A copy of the CSFC Mortgage is attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;57&rdquo;.</BOLD></P>
<P><BOLD>159.</BOLD> In connection with the acquisition of the Waterloo Lands, Schembri executed:
<P1>(a) a resolution dated April 24, 2008 authorizing the acquisition of the Waterloo Lands; and</P1>
<P1>(b) a resolution dated April 23, 2008 authorizing the CSFC Mortgage.</P1></P>
<P>Copies of these resolutions are attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;58&rdquo;.</BOLD></P>
<P><BOLD>160.</BOLD> At the time that 359 King acquired the Waterloo Lands, the houses thereon were rented to tenants. Another one of my companies (namely, Kinsgley Management Inc.) administered to these tenancies going forward.</P></BLOCK1>
<BLOCK1><N>22</N><TI>Maas APS</TI>
<P><BOLD>161.</BOLD> On or around June 18, 2008,172 entered into an agreement of purchase and sale (the <BOLD>&ldquo;Maas APS&rdquo;)</BOLD> with Sean Maas <BOLD>(&ldquo;Maas&rdquo;)</BOLD> providing for the completion of a sale of the JV Lands (now consolidated and known municipally as 345 King Street North, Waterloo) &ldquo;14 days following the date that occupancy approval is granted by the [City] for the intended project herein&rdquo;. A copy of the Maas APS is attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;59&rdquo;.</BOLD></P>
<P><BOLD>162.</BOLD> Over the next month or so, 172 and Maas executed two amendments and a notice of fulfillment of condition resulting in the Maas APS becoming firm and binding. Copies of these documents are attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;60&rdquo;.</BOLD></P>
<P><BOLD>163.</BOLD> Around the time that the Maas APS became firm and binding, Schembri and I agreed to roll the profits of the JV Project into Triumph and then to the Triumph Subsidiaries (the <BOLD>&ldquo;Rollover Agreement&rdquo;).</BOLD></P>
