<BLOCK1><N>37</N><TI>Schembri Commences Litigation</TI>
<P><BOLD>226.</BOLD> Schembri commenced the Main Action in Toronto in February, 2010. The Main Action was transferred to Kitchener in 2011. Schembri has been represented throughout by Wortzman.</P>
<P><BOLD>227.</BOLD> The Main Action is defended. I (along with my companies) am represented by Heath Whiteley <BOLD>(&ldquo;Whiteley&rdquo;),</BOLD> formerly of Gowlings LLP <BOLD>(&ldquo;Gowlings&rdquo;)</BOLD> in Toronto and now a sole practitioner. Whiteley has been involved in the Main Action since the fall of 2010. Patterson is now represented by Richard Campbell in Waterloo, following the retirement of Gary Petker. The Way Family Trust has been represented throughout by Ian Hull at Hull &amp; Hull in Toronto.</P>
<P><BOLD>228.</BOLD> In addition to defending the Main Action, I have asserted a counterclaim, initially in part, to the effect that Schembri Financial and Schembri breached the Shareholder Agreement by failing to comply with the right of first refusal (in the ROFR Clause) so as to allow me to participate in the acquisition and development of other properties located in Waterloo Region. The damages suffered by me resulting from Schembri's breach of the ROFR Provisions subsequently became the subject matter of the ROFR Action.</P></BLOCK1>
<BLOCK1><N>38</N><TI>MIK Litigation</TI>
<P><BOLD>229.</BOLD> aDupuis represented Jamesway in responding to the statement of claim of MIK in connection with the MIK Lien (the <BOLD>&ldquo;MIK Litigation&rdquo;).</BOLD> Ultimately, the MIK Litigation was concluded in favour of Jamesway, with the claim of MIK being dismissed and the counterclaim of Jamesway being granted. Copies of the documents relating to the disposition of the MIK Litigation are attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;100&rdquo;.</BOLD></P>
<P><BOLD>230.</BOLD> I am informed by Patterson and believe that she obtained the cell phone records for the cell phone number provided to Dupuis and paid for by Jamesway. I am further informed by Patterson and believe that these records show calls between Dupuis and Schembri in late January and early February, 2010.</P></BLOCK1>
<BLOCK1><N>39</N><TI>Directors' Meeting re Triumph and Simcoe &amp; Eastwood</TI>
