to be held on April 12, 2010 at Volpini's offices. A copy ofthis letter and the enclosures thereto are attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;101&rdquo;.</BOLD> Copies of the minutes of these two board meetings are attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;102&rdquo;.</BOLD></P>
<P><BOLD>232.</BOLD> I learned subsequently that Schembri had acquired and was developing a property municipally known as 33 Taylorwood Road, Oshawa (the <BOLD>&ldquo;Taylorwood Property&rdquo;)</BOLD> at that time of the Director's Meeting. The Taylorwood Property is located approximately four hundred feet (400') from the Oshawa Lands. Copies of documents evidencing Schembri's interest in the Taylorwood Property and its' subsequent sale are attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;103&rdquo;.</BOLD></P>
<P><BOLD>233.</BOLD> Schembri did not disclose his interest in the Taylorwood Property to me, or to the Court in connection with his receivership motion. Accordingly, I believe Schembri acted in bad faith in attempting to block development of the Oshawa Lands until he completed his development of the Taylorwood Property.</P></BLOCK1>
