<P><BOLD>235.</BOLD> Schembri refused to pay. I did not seize his shares.</P></BLOCK1>
<BLOCK1><N>41</N><TI>Schembri Blocks Arbitration</TI>
<P><BOLD>236.</BOLD> In furtherance of the arbitration provision in paragraph 15 of the Shareholder Agreement, I caused Triumph to serve a Notice Demanding Arbitration dated June 25, 2010 (the <BOLD>&ldquo;Arbitration Notice&rdquo;),</BOLD> leading to an exchange of correspondence between counsel for Schembri and my counsel regarding the Arbitration Notice, and then service of a Notice of Motion by counsel for Schembri. A copy of the Arbitration Notice along with the correspondence exchanged in connection therewith is attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;104&rdquo;.</BOLD> A copy of the Notice of Motion served by counsel for Schembri is attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;105&rdquo;.</BOLD></P>
<P><BOLD>237.</BOLD> I learned subsequently that Schembri did not swear the affidavit referenced in his Notice of Motion. A copy of the correspondence sent by Whiteley to counsel for Schembri on July 25, 2011 and August 31, 2011 evidencing what I learned subsequently is attached and marked hereto as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;106&rdquo;.</BOLD></P></BLOCK1>
<BLOCK1><N>42</N><TI>The Receivership Motion</TI>
<P><BOLD>238.</BOLD> On a motion by Schembri, Madam Justice Roberts appointed a receiver (the <BOLD>&ldquo;Receiver&rdquo;)</BOLD> over the Triumph Lands. In the Reasons of Madam Justice Roberts dated September 24, 2010, her Honour made several adverse findings against me, with the caveat at paragraph 38 as follows:
<QUOTE><P><EM>&ldquo;While there is strong prima facie evidence that the defendants' conduct has been inappropriate and possibly egregious</EM>, <BOLD><EM>as this is an interlocutory proceeding, I have not made any final conclusions concerning their behaviour. It is therefore premature for me at this stage to award substantial indemnity costs on the basis of facts that have not yet been finally determined</EM>.</BOLD> (emphasis added)</P></QUOTE></P>
<P><BOLD>239.</BOLD> Contrary to her Honour's various adverse findings:
<P1>(a) the evidence provided by Schembri was disputed;</P1>
<P1>(b) I did not grossly inflate the amounts of various changes as alleged by Dupuis under oath;</P1>
<P1>(c) I did not add to change orders hundreds of hours for labour that were not expended on the JV Project;</P1>
<P1>(d) the vast majority of the work was not carried out by the Way Group; and</P1>
<P1>(e) there was no improper transfer of $6 million to Premier.</P1></P>
<P>I address each of the foregoing erroneous findings below.</P>
<BLOCK2><TI>Schembri's Evidence Disputed</TI>
<P><BOLD>240.</BOLD> In paragraph 6 of my affidavit sworn May 14, 2010 (the <BOLD>&ldquo;Way May 2010 Affidavit&rdquo;)</BOLD> in response to the Schembri April 2010 Affidavit, I stated the following:
<QUOTE><P><EM>I disagree with the truth and accuracy of many of the &ldquo;facts&rdquo; put forward by the</EM> [Schembri April 2010 Affidavit]. <EM>However, for the purposes of these motions, I only put forward contrary evidence with respect to those untruths and inaccuracies that may bear upon the issues raised by these motions and those that are most offensive to me. A failure to challengeor contradict the</EM> [Schembri April 2010 Affidavit] <EM>here does not mean that I agree with or accept the evidence put forth by the</EM> [Schembri April 2010 Affidavit]. (italics added)</P></QUOTE></P>
<P>I then proceeded to dispute numerous aspects of Schembri's evidence. A copy of the Way May 2010 Affidavit is attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;107&rdquo;.</BOLD></P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI>Dupuis' Evidence re Change Orders</TI>
<P><BOLD>241.</BOLD> I did not grossly inflate the amounts of various change orders by adding:
<P1>(a) unauthorized and excessive administrative fees; or</P1>
<P1>(b) hundreds of hours for labour that were not expended on the JV Project.</P1></P>
<P><BOLD>242.</BOLD> Change orders were prepared by various employees of Jamesway. It is my practice to instruct Jamesway employees to make sure that they capture all costs associated with a change order.</P>
<P><BOLD>243.</BOLD> I am informed by Crozier that Jonas is able to generate a report detailing the hours spent by Jamesway employees; as well as other reports showing costs incurred to third parties. A copy of the Jonas report detailing the hours spent by Jamesway employees in connection with the change order is attached hereto and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;108&rdquo;.</BOLD> This report was provided previously in an answer to an undertaking.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI>The Majority of Work on the JV Project Was Performed by Third Parties</TI>
<P><BOLD>244.</BOLD> As I stated in paragraph 17 of the Way May 2010 Affidavit, &ldquo;the vast majority of the construction of the [JV] Project was carried out by third party contractors&rdquo;. Schembri knows this.</P>
