<BLOCK2><N>IV.</N><TI>Schembri's Representations re the 2014 Schembri ROFR SJ Motion</TI>
<P><BOLD>76.</BOLD> In an effort to further delay the Main Action and delay the ROFR Action, Schembri represented repeatedly in 2014 that he was bringing a motion for summary judgment in the ROFR Action (the <BOLD>&ldquo;2014 Schembri ROFR SJ Motion&rdquo;)</BOLD>.<FOOTNOTE><FREEFORM><P>Way Affidavit, RMR, Volume 1, Tab A, pages 91, paragraphs 326 and 327</P></FREEFORM></FOOTNOTE></P>
<P><BOLD>77.</BOLD> Particulars of the repeated representations in connection with the 2014 Schembri ROFR SJ Motion include<FOOTNOTE><FREEFORM><P>Way Affidavit, RMR, Volume 1, Tab A, page 92, paragraphs 328 and 329</P>
<P>Way Affidavit, RMR, Volume 10, Tabs 133 and 134, Exhibits &ldquo;133&rdquo; and &ldquo;134&rdquo; at pages 2716, 2731 and 2739</P></FREEFORM></FOOTNOTE>:
