<P1><BOLD>Wortzman's letter dated July 9, 2014</BOLD></P1>
<QUOTE><P><EM>I am finalizing the motion record for partial summary judgment</EM>.</P></QUOTE></P>
<P><BOLD>78.</BOLD> As a result of Schembri's representations, Way was forced to obtain a timetabling order (the <BOLD>&ldquo;ROFR Timetable Order&rdquo;)</BOLD> in the ROFR Action (that set a schedule for the conduct of the 2014 Schembri ROFR SJ Motion) and a third timetabling order in the Main Action (that set dates for examinations for discovery having regard to the schedule for the 2014 Schembri ROFR SJ Motion).<FOOTNOTE><FREEFORM><P>Way Affidavit, RMR, Volume 1, Tab A, pages 90 to 92, paragraphs 324, 325, 330 and 311</P>
<P>Way Affidavit, RMR, Volume 10, Tabs 132, 133 and 135, Exhibits &ldquo;132&rdquo;, &ldquo;133&rdquo; and &ldquo;135&rdquo;</P></FREEFORM></FOOTNOTE></P>
<P><BOLD>79.</BOLD> Despite Schembri's repeated representations over an extended period of time he never brought the 2014 Schembri ROFR SJ Motion. It is plain and obvious that Schembri intentionally deceived the Way Group and the Court for the purpose of avoiding his examination for discovery (thereby delaying the Main Action and the ROFR Action) and increasing the amount of costs being incurred by Way.<FOOTNOTE><FREEFORM><P>Way Affidavit, RMR, Volume 1, Tab A, pages 92 and 93, paragraphs 330 and 331</P></FREEFORM></FOOTNOTE></P>
<P><BOLD>80.</BOLD> Schembri never explained his deception, nor sought any amendments to the ROFR Timetable Order.<FOOTNOTE><FREEFORM><P>Way Affidavit, RMR, Volume 1, Tab A, pages 92 and 93, paragraph 331</P></FREEFORM></FOOTNOTE></P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><N>V.</N><TI>Schembri's Breach of the Rules of Civil Procedure</TI>
<BLOCK3><N>A.</N><TI>Schembri's Refusal to Produce Relevant Documents</TI>
<P><BOLD>81.</BOLD> At the time that Schembri's breach of the ROFR Clause was the subject matter of the counterclaim in Main Action, Schembri swore:
<P1>(a) an affidavit of documents on October 6, 2010 listing 181 documents in Schedule &ldquo;A&rdquo; and no documents in Schedule &ldquo;B&rdquo; (the <BOLD>&ldquo;Schembri Main Action AoD&rdquo;);</BOLD> and</P1>
<P1>(b) a supplementary affidavit of documents on August 1, 2012 listing:
<P2>(i) 146 documents in Schedule &ldquo;A&rdquo; (of which only 4 documents appear to be dated after the Schembri Main Action AoD); and</P2>
<P2>(ii) 2 documents in Schedule &ldquo;B&rdquo; (that were listed in Schedule A.3 of the Way Main Action AoD but not in the Schembri Main Action AoD)</P2></P1>
<P1>(the <BOLD>&ldquo;Schembri Main Action Supp AoD&rdquo;)</BOLD>.<FOOTNOTE><FREEFORM><P>Way Affidavit, RMR, Volume 1, Tab A, pages 80 to 82, paragraphs 283 and 291</P>
<P>Way Affidavit, RMR, Volume 9, Tabs 123 and 124, Exhibits &ldquo;123&rdquo; and &ldquo;124&rdquo;</P></FREEFORM></FOOTNOTE></P1></P>
<P><BOLD>82.</BOLD> Of note, the Schembri Main Action AoD listed the agreement of purchase and sale for 59 Columbia Street West, Waterloo.</P>
<P><BOLD>83.</BOLD> Approximately two years after receiving the Statement of Claim in the ROFR Action, Schembri finally served a Statement of Defence (as stated in paragraph 43 above) and swore an affidavit of documents in the ROFR Action on September 30, 2014 (the <BOLD>&ldquo;Schembri ROFR AoD&rdquo;)</BOLD>. By that time the Schembri Group had completed the acquisitions of the twenty-seven properties that are the subject matter of the ROFR Breaches. Of these twenty-seven properties, the Schembri Group has produced only one agreement of purchase and sale (as stated in paragraph 82 above).<FOOTNOTE><FREEFORM><P>Way Affidavit, RMR, Volume 1, Tab A, page 9, paragraph 29</P>
<P>Way Affidavit, RMR, Volume 1, Tabs 2, Exhibit &ldquo;2&rdquo;</P></FREEFORM></FOOTNOTE></P>
