<P><BOLD>85.</BOLD> Asis evident from the transcript of the cross-examination of Schembri conducted on September 17, 2018, his counsel acknowledged there were proper questions that would be answered should the within motion be unsuccessful.</P></BLOCK3></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><N>VI.</N><TI>Schembri's Improper Use of Interlocutory Decisions</TI>
<P><BOLD>86.</BOLD> The Schembri Group relies on certain interlocutory decisions made in 2010 and 2011 to support their motion to dismiss the ROFR Action. Such reliance is not only improper, it highlights their inordinate delay in bringing this motion when Schembri has set the Main Action down for trial.</P>
<P><BOLD>87.</BOLD> As stated in paragraph 36 above, the Honourable Justice Roberts expressly noted in her Endorsement dated September 24, 2010 (appointing a receiver over the three subsidiaries of Triumph) that <BOLD><EM>&ldquo;as this is an interlocutory proceeding, I have not made any final conclusions...&rdquo;</EM></BOLD> [emphasis added]</P>
<P><BOLD>88.</BOLD> Contrary to paragraph 35(d) of the affidavit sworn by Schembri and paragraph 36(d) of the factum of the Schembri Group, Justice Roberts stated in paragraph 8 of her Honour's Endorsment that <BOLD><EM>&ldquo;it appears that</EM></BOLD> <EM>Mr. Way added to change orders hundereds of hours for labour that were not expended...&rdquo;</EM> [emphasis added].</P>
<P><BOLD>89.</BOLD> That is not true. More importantly, the evidence of the individual that Justice Roberts relied on (namely, Rejean Dupuis) was contradicted by that individual's own sworn evidence in two separate affidavits filed with the Court that resulted in two judgments being granted to 172 in connection with a proceeding relating to the JV Project.<FOOTNOTE><FREEFORM><P>Way Affidavit, RMR, Volume 1, Tab A, pages 63, 66 and 67, paragraphs 229, and 239 to 243</P>
<P>Way Affidavit, RMR, Volume 7, Tabs 100, 107 and 108, Exhibits &ldquo;100&rdquo; at pages 1818 to 1851, &ldquo;107&rdquo; and &ldquo;108&rdquo;</P></FREEFORM></FOOTNOTE></P>
<P><BOLD>90.</BOLD> Similarly, the Honourable Justice Mesbur expressly noted in her Endorsement dated July 18, 2011 (dismissing Schembri's motion re the Oshawa Lands) that <BOLD>Schembri</BOLD> <BOLD><EM>&ldquo;has made serious allegations of impropriety against [Mr. Way]. It remains to be seen whether they are accurate or not&rdquo;</EM></BOLD>. [emphasis added]<FOOTNOTE><FREEFORM><P>Way Affidavit, RMR, Volume 9, Tabs 117, Exhibit &ldquo;117&rdquo; at page 2440, paragraph 13</P></FREEFORM></FOOTNOTE></P></BLOCK2>
