<P1>(a) the defendants:
<P2>(i) withdrawing certain allegations that the plaintiff, Al Way <BOLD>(&ldquo;Way&rdquo;)</BOLD> and his companies have committed fraud (the <BOLD>&ldquo;Withdrawn Fraud Allegations&rdquo;);</BOLD> and</P2>
<P2>(ii) abandoning their &ldquo;fall back&rdquo; position that was based on the Withdrawn Fraud Allegations (the <BOLD>&ldquo;Abandoned Fallback Position&rdquo;);</BOLD></P2>
without notice, and while counsel was in the midst of oral submissions methodically refuting the Withdrawn Fraud Allegations; and</P1>
<P1>(b) the request of the Honourable Mr. Justice Sloan sent October 22, 2018.</P1></P>
<P><BOLD>2.</BOLD> The Withdrawn Fraud Allegations and the Abandoned Fallback Position are simply another scorched earth litigation tactic in a series of scorched earth litigation tactics that Schembri has been engaged in for more than eight years in furtherance of his efforts to bankrupt Way; while Schembri amasses significant wealth through the acquisition of at least twenty-eight properties in Waterloo Region in breach of:
