<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I">AFFIDAVIT OF ALVEN J. WAY (sworn January 18, 2018)</TI>
<P><BOLD>I, ALVEN J. WAY,</BOLD> businessman, of the City of Waterloo, in the Province of Ontario, make oath and say as follows.</P>
<BLOCK2><N>A.</N><TI>Preliminary Comments</TI>
<P>1. I am a plaintiff, and a director of each of the corporate plaintiffs, in this proceeding (the <BOLD>&ldquo;ROFR Action&rdquo;</BOLD>), and a defendant, plaintiff by counterclaim in a related action bearing Court File No Court File No. C-42-11 (the &ldquo;Main Action&rdquo;). I am being sued personally in the Main Action for at least $30,000,000. As such, I have personal knowledge of the facts deposed to herein except where knowledge of such facts is stated to be on information and belief and, where so stated, I verily believe those facts to be true.</P>
<P>2. Previously, I swore an affidavit on September 16, 2016 (the <BOLD>&ldquo;September 2016 Affidavit&rdquo;)</BOLD> in support of a request for an order, among other things, requiring the plaintiff, Gordon Schembri (&ldquo;Schembri&rdquo;) to attend his examination for discovery for three weeks on fixed dates in late 2016. Attached and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo;</BOLD> hereto is a true copy of the September 2016 Affidavit, without exhibits.</P>
<P>3. Unless otherwise defined herein, defined terms shall have the same meaning as defined in the September 2016 Affidavit. All dates referred to herein relate to 2017 unless stated otherwise.</P>
<P>4. I repeat and rely on the September 2016 Affidavit in support of the request of the plaintiffs at this time for an order:
<P1>(a) that the order of the Local Registrar dated May 25, 2017 dismissing the within action for delay be set aside;</P1>
<P1>(b) requiring Schembri to attend his examination for discovery in the Main Action and in the ROFR Action on February 12th through 23rd, inclusive, or such other and further dates as may be fixed by this Honourable Court; and</P1>
<P1>(c) costs of this motion on a substantial indemnity basis payable forthwith.</P1></P>
<P>5. This motion is being brought as efforts by my counsel to reach a resolution with counsel for Schembri in respect of the foregoing relief have been unsuccessful. Attached and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo;</BOLD> hereto are true copies of the correspondence exchanged between my counsel and counsel for Schembri since June.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><N>B.</N><TI>Background to Motion</TI>
<P>6. As provided for in the Orders (2) of Justice Broad dated September 4, 2014 in the Main Action and in the ROFR Action (attached as Exhibits &ldquo;E&rdquo; and &ldquo;F&rdquo; to the September 2016 Affidavit), the Main Action and the ROFR Action are to be tried together.</P>
<P>7. Counsel for Schembri completed my examination for discovery in the Main Action and the ROFR Action on April 26<SUP>th</SUP>. Subsequently, Schembri set the Main Action down for trial.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><N>C.</N><TI>The Registrar's Dismissal Order</TI>
<P>8. I am informed by Whiteley and believe that he was informed by counsel for Schembri in June that the ROFR Action had been dismissed for delay by the Registrar. I am further informed by Whiteley and believe that that was the first notice that he received of the Registrar's dismissal of the ROFR Action. Attached and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;C&rdquo;</BOLD> hereto is a true copy of the Order Dismissing Action for Delay dated May 25, 2017 provided by counsel for Schembri on July 26, 2017.</P>
<P>9. I am informed by Whiteley and believe that Schembri will consent to the Dismissal Order being set aside provided that I agree to a timetable for the conduct of a motion by Schembri in the ROFR Action for summary judgment (the <BOLD>&ldquo;Schembri ROFR SJ Motion&rdquo;).</BOLD></P>
<P>10. I do not agree to a timetable being set for the Schembri ROFR SJ Motion for three reasons.</P>
<P>11. First, setting a timetable ignores the relief sought in the September 2016 Affidavit that Schembri be prohibited from bringing a motion for summary judgment, in whole or in part.</P>
<P>12. Secondly, my counsel has yet to complete the examination for discovery of Schembri, whereas counsel for Schembri has completed an examination for discovery of me (in both the Main Action and the ROFR Action). In total, my examination for discovery in the Main Action and the ROFR Action took place over eighteen days and I was asked more than fifteen thousand questions.</P>
<P>13. Thirdly, as stated in paragraph 12 of the September 2016 Affidavit, I believe that Schembri has failed to comply with the Rules of Civil Procedure concerning documentary disclosure.</P>
<P>14. I have learned subsequently that Schembri caused the property purchased by the defendant, 5 Rittenhouse Inc., to be sold. I am informed by Whiteley and believe that 5 Rittenhouse Inc. has not produced any documents whatsoever relating to the purchase and sale of this property as appears from the Affidavit of Documents sworn September 30, 2014 by Schembri (being Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo; to the September 2016 Affidavit).</P>
<P>15. In June, I was informed by Joe Benninger, a real estate agent in Kitchener-Waterloo, and believe that Schembri: (a) purchased a property at the corner of Bridgeport Road and Weber Street in Waterloo with the intent to build a high-rise apartment building; and (b) owned another property in Kitchener on which he is constructing a medical building. I am informed by Whiteley and believe that Schembri has not produced any documents relating to the purchases of these properties.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><N>D.</N><TI>Examination for Discovery of Schembri</TI>
<P>16. Today I have sworn an affidavit in the Main Action, among other things, addressing the background to and history of the examination for discovery of Schembri, along with the extensive efforts by my counsel to continue with that examination at the earliest possible opportunity (the <BOLD>&ldquo;Main Action Affidavit&rdquo;).</BOLD> Attached and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;D&rdquo;</BOLD> hereto is a true copy of the Main Action Affidavit, without exhibits.</P>
<P>17. I repeat and rely on the Main Action Affidavit in support of the request herein that Schembri attend for discovery on February 12th through 23rd, inclusive, or such other and further dates as may be fixed by this Honourable Court.</P>
<P>18. I swear this affidavit for the purpose stated in paragraph 2 above, and for no other improper purpose.</P>
