<P><BOLD>THE MOTION IS FOR</BOLD>
<P1>(a) If necessary, an Order granting leave to bring this motion and a motion in Court File No. C-42-11;</P1>
<P1>(b) An Order directing the Registrar of the Superior Court of Justice, Kitchener, to issue and enter the draft Order attached hereto as <BOLD>Schedule &ldquo;A&rdquo;;</BOLD></P1>
<P1>(c) An Order setting a timetable for the Defendants' Summary Judgment motion in the form attached hereto as Schedule <BOLD>&ldquo;B&rdquo;</BOLD> or such other timetable as the Court considers just;</P1>
<P1>(d) Such further and other relief as lawyers may advise and this Honourable Court deem just.</P1></P>
<P><BOLD>THE GROUNDS FOR THE MOTION ARE</BOLD>
<P1>(a) This Action (the &ldquo;ROFR Action&rdquo;) is a companion Action to Court File no. C-42-11 (the &ldquo;Main Action&rdquo;);</P1>
<P1>(b) By Order of this Honourable Court, the ROFR Action and Main Action are to be tried together;</P1>
<P1>(c) On May 18, 2017, the Defendants to the ROFR Action served a motion record in support of a summary judgment motion (the &ldquo;ROFR SJ Motion&rdquo;);</P1>
<P1>(d) On May 19, 2017, the Honourable Mr. Justice Sloan granted an Order allowing the Plaintiffs in the Main Action to set the Main Action down for Trial without prejudice to their rights to bring the ROFR SJ Motion;</P1>
<P1>(e) Counsel for the Plaintiffs in the ROFR Action will not approve the draft Order prepared by the Defendants (which reflects the May 19, 2017 Order of Justice Sloan);</P1>
<P1>(f) The ROFR Action was dismissed as a result of delay by the Registrar on May 25, 2017 (the &ldquo;Dismissal Order&rdquo;);</P1>
<P1>(g) As a result of the ROFR Action being dismissed, the Plaintiffs in the Main Action served and filed their Trial Record in the Main Action;</P1>
<P1>(h) The Plaintiffs to the ROFR Action seek an Order to set aside the Dismissal Order but waited over 7 months before bringing a motion to do so;</P1>
<P1>(i) The Defendants to the ROFR Action have repeatedly advised the Plaintiffs to the ROFR Action that they would consent to an Order setting aside the Dismissal Order, subject to the Plaintiffs agreeing to a timetable for the ROFR SJ Motion;</P1>
